Starting 2023 with some truth-telling. 2022 I faced a lot of struggles both emotionally, physically, and mentally. For a while, I was not in the state of mind to do anything, but I forced myself to keep going because I knew being idle in a whirlwind of negative thoughts would not bring me any good. So I pushed on. But then I got sick in August and was sick for ten days, lost over 10 pounds, and was not very active. This gave me the necessary rest(even though it was forced) to re-examine my life.

I knew I had to make a change not only for myself but also for the energy I was bringing to the world around me. I started my foundational practices, meditating, starting a skin care routine, learning Spanish, and journalling every single day. A practice that invigorated and motivated me and brought me to a new positive headspace. I continue those practices as well as working out, skill building, course taking, reading, listening exercises, asking questions exercises, and so much more.

So here I am writing my 2023 Mindset pack, not resolutions that we tend not to keep, not goals we tend not to look at till the end of the year, but rather mindset, a way of being and living that focuses on your inner world as much as your outer.

2023 is going to be great, people, we have gone through the worst, and although some of you might not see the light yet, it will happen. I promise it will.

Sending you all love❤️and successful mindsets for 2023!

Happy St. Patricks Day! 🍀We got a little creative with our cocktails and made a Whisky Mojito using an 🇮🇪Irish-American bottle of @keepersheartwhiskey

We absolutely loved the blend of American and Irish Whiskey, creating a smooth, supple, and delicious taste of candied ginger, 😍vanilla, and an oaky finish that really brings it all together.

Here is the recipe:

Ingredients:
1 oz Keepers Heart Whiskey
1 tsp lime juice
2 oz soda water
1/2 oz green creme de menthe
3 dashes of Angostura bitters

Steps:
Pack a Collins glass full of crushed Ice, mix the Creme de menthe with
soda water and the bitters and lime together and pour over the top. 
Wait a moment for them to settle, and then top with Keerps Heart Whiskey.
